verbose_text: However, if not controlled adequately, the expression of chemokines such as CXCL-9 and CXCL-10 at a high level (XREF_TABLE) later in the process, when no more infectious virus is detected within the brain, could contribute to the recruitment of more and more immune cells, a situation that could lead to an autoimmune response partly related to the presence of MBP-autoreactive T cells.
